  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The resolution by Councilman\nPratt last night that steps be taken\nfor the forfeiture of the Roger Will\nliams gas franchise. granted in\nMay, 1904, was referred to the COM\nmittee of the whole. The Williams\ninterests were recently sold to the\nSpokane Falls Gas Light Co. The\nfranchise prohibits consolidation.\nWilliams agreed to furnish gas to\nthe public for not more than $3.50.\nHe built about eight miles of mains\nand only furnished the product to\nthe old company. 1t was on Mr..\nPratt's request that the council re-\nferred the resolution to the COM\nmittee Of the whole."
    }
  ]
